#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'CHECKLIST'
Skald Linux release validation checklist

Automated before publish:
- just check
- just release-archives
- just release-smoke
- just release-checksums
- just release-sign

Manual clean install:
- Verify archive checksum and signature.
- Extract archive into a temporary directory.
- Install binaries to ~/.local/bin or another user-local bin directory.
- Run skald version --json and skaldd --build-info-json.
- Run skald setup or skald config init plus the selected profile.
- Run skald doctor.
- Install and start the systemd user service.

Manual upgrade:
- Preserve ~/.config/skald, ~/.local/share/skald/models, styles, apps, snippets, and keyring entries.
- Stop skaldd.service.
- Replace binaries from the new archive.
- Run skald config upgrade.
- Run skald service install and systemctl --user restart skaldd.service.
- Run skald doctor.

Manual rollback:
- Stop skaldd.service.
- Replace binaries from the previous signed archive.
- Restore config from backup if the newer version performed irreversible migrations.
- Run skald service install and systemctl --user restart skaldd.service.
- Run skald doctor.

Functional validation:
- CPU doctor output on the CPU-safe archive.
- CUDA doctor output on the CUDA archive and tested NVIDIA driver.
- Microphone capture.
- Final local transcription.
- Clipboard delivery.
- Safe-paste fallback and target-change handling.
- Overlay text mode.
- Overlay visualizer mode.
- Tray starts or fails clearly when StatusNotifier/AppIndicator is unavailable.
- Cleanup remains disabled by default.
- Desktop matrix notes updated for tested Hyprland, GNOME, KDE, Sway, X11, and headless limitations.
- Release notes list known desktop, GPU, CUDA, signing, and packaging limitations.
- Artifacts and logs contain no model weights, audio, transcript text, user config, API keys, or proprietary CUDA libraries.
CHECKLIST
